# UI Verification After Changes

**After ANY change to UI components, CSS, styling, or layout, you MUST verify visually before committing.**

## When This Applies

This is MANDATORY after editing:
- Any file in `components/ui/`
- Any file in `components/shell/`
- `app/globals.css` or any CSS file
- `lib/theme/mantine-theme.ts`
- `components/providers/MantineClientProvider.tsx`
- Any component that renders visible UI (cards, forms, pages)

## Verification Steps

1. **Start Playwright browser** (NOT the Cursor IDE browser - it has dark mode that gives false results)
2. **Screenshot these 3 pages:**
   - `/dashboard` - Tests dashboard cards, sidebar, header
   - `/characters` - Tests entity list cards, buttons
   - `/characters/new` - Tests form inputs, Card wrapper, buttons
3. **Check each screenshot for:**
   - All backgrounds are white/light (no dark mode leak)
   - All text is dark on light background (readable)
   - Buttons are solid cyan (no gradients)
   - Input fields have visible borders
   - Cards have subtle borders and shadows
4. **Show screenshots to user** before committing

